description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work within an innovative division which has many new services including the Intermediate Tier Service.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Wolstenholme Intermediate Care Unit is a 24 bedded community based enhanced care setting based within a purpose built single room environment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The staff working on the unit are from a social and healthcare background with therapists/social workers and partner agencies working with an integrated and seamless approach.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Evidence of a genuine interest in nursing the older client group and focusing on person centred care is essential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be joining a well-established team and will be provided with a tailored supernumerary induction tailored to meet your needs. It is a requirement that you are able to multi task and prioritise your workload with efficacy. Excellent inter-personal communication skills are an essential requirement and the positive attitude and attributes necessary for a creative and forward thinking team member will be necessary&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to gain experience in the speciality of rehabilitation. Internal rotation, day or night duty considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supported throughout with regular one to one supervisions and NMC Revalidation preparation and opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Sophie Ramsbottom&lt;/p&gt;
